<h4 id="two-different-view-of-thinking-of-curves">two different view of thinking of curves</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Cartesian form: a line is $l: ax+by+c=0$</li>
  <li>Parameter form: $l: (a+tx,b+ty)$</li>
  <li>ancient greek mathemation think curves purly geometry objects.</li>
  <li>17th century mathmatain think they can be algebraic objects. or could be parameter objects.</li>
</ol>

