<h4 id="terminology-algebraic-curve">Terminology: algebraic curve</h4>
<p>A curve with an equation:
\(P(x,y) = 0\)
where p is a ploynomial in x,y, usually with rational coefficients, which called algebraic curve.</p>

<h4 id="question-can-we-parametrize-higher-degree-curves">Question: can we parametrize higher degree curves?</h4>
<ol>
  <li>this question is fundamental and natural.</li>
</ol>

